CBRE Melbourne Strip Retail Investments are proud to present to the market, 34 Chapel Street, Windsor being offered for sale via Public On-Site Auction Thursday 31st August at 12:30pm.

We highlight some key points below:

- Strategically positioned in the heart of the eclectic Chapel Street, Windsor hospitality precinct, home to some of Melbourne's most popular restaurants, cafes and bars

- A highly convenient retail location, only metres from Windsor Train Station and serviced by over 100 council car parks*

- Situated on an irreplaceable 214sqm* allotment with dual access and on-site parking

- New 5 year lease to the highly popular Southside Central

- Net annual income of $125,000 + GSt + Outgoings with fixed 3% annual rental increases

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: POSITIONED IN THE HEART OF MELBOURNE'S HOTTEST RETAIL & HOSPITALITY PRECINCT

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located on Chapel Street just metres back from the corner of High Street in the fully restored iconic Heritage Building, this is a terrific opportunity for a retailer to establish their business. 

Nestled amongst renowned shopping, stylish cafes, dining and legendary bars and nightlife.

Surrounding tenants include 7-Eleven, Morris Jones, KX Pilates Grill'd, Mr Miyagi, Hawker Hall, Fonda, Hannoi Hannah, Journeyman Cafe and many more! 

174 Chapel Street - 73sqm*
178 Chapel Street - 67sqm*

Available now!

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: TWO WINDSOR RETAIL SHOPS FOR LEASE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located at the Gateway of the fast emerging and sought after Chapel Street Windsor Retail Precinct, three doors from High Street corner. This near new shop is within a fully restored iconic Heritage Building and is amongst world renowned shopping, stylish cafes, dining and legendary bars and nightlife.
